jruff - A fast Java linter with auto-fix support

This project is a fork of Ruff (https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff),
an extremely fast Python linter and code formatter, written in Rust.

The following components are derived from Ruff:
- crates/jruff_text_size - Text size and range utilities
- crates/jruff_source_file - Source file handling and line indexing
- crates/jruff_diagnostics - Diagnostic and fix infrastructure

Original Ruff authors and contributors:
- Charlie Marsh <charlie.r.marsh@gmail.com>
- Astral Software Inc.
- And all Ruff contributors (https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff/graphs/contributors)

Ruff is licensed under the MIT License:
https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff/blob/main/LICENSE

We are grateful to the Ruff team for creating such excellent infrastructure
that made this project possible.
